<anchor id="fram_8h_1fram"/> <simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>FRAM chip is connected to nRF9160 via SPI bus. FRAM is used to store the acceleration raw data. FRAM has 512 byte storage capacity. In one measurement cycle (15 measurements in an one second cycle with sampling rate of 4400Hz) the capacity of the FRAM is nearly exhausted (). Therefore a measurement cycle has been limited to 15 seconds. <linebreak/>
 To be able to calculate displacement data the FRAM raw data storage must be reduced to 5 seconds measurement, so that there is enough space to store intermediate and final displacement data. The memory layout is therefore separated in three blocks (see section <ref refid="_m_s_c_1SectionDisplacement" kindref="member">Displacement Calculation</ref> for further details). <image type="html" name="FramLayout.png" inline="yes"></image>
 <linebreak/>
 See MB85RS4MTY data sheet, page 5 for SPI connection.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para>This source code is confidential and proprietary information of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. You may not disclose, copy, or distribute this source code or any part thereof without the explicit permission of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
